What is the difference between the terms keyword and argument in the IOS command structure?
A)A keyword is a specific parameter. An argument is not a predefined variable.
B)A keyword always appears directly after a command. An argument does not.
C)A keyword is required to complete a command. An argument is not.
D)A keyword is entered with a predefined length. An argument can be any length.
A


